":{"absolutePath":"/workspace/UsefulResourceRepo2.0/_RESOURCES/awesome-git-user/blogsite/src/images/react.svg"}},{"node":{"absolutePath":"/workspace/UsefulResourceRepo2.0/_RESOURCES/awesome-git-user/blogsite/src/images/scikit-learn.svg"}},{"node":{"absolutePath":"/workspace/UsefulResourceRepo2.0/_RESOURCES/awesome-git-user/blogsite/src/images/stackoverflow.svg"}},{"node":{"absolutePath":"/workspace/UsefulResourceRepo2.0/_RESOURCES/awesome-git-user/blogsite/src/images/twitter.svg"}},{"node":{"absolutePath":"/workspace/UsefulResourceRepo2.0/_RESOURCES/awesome-git-user/blogsite/src/images/youtube.svg"}},{"node":{"absolutePath":"/workspace/UsefulResourceRepo2.0/_RESOURCES/awesome-git-user/blogsite/src/images/nodejs.svg"}}]},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/d6830116d38db26b5dc1fd9de302689d/css3.svg"}}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/bef99f4fec06bf262ea185b92937109e/github_tech.svg"}}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/5808d5df5cd92a9ba64a0905e7a9c55a/d3js.svg"}}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/66762bbba1ef9c8fdc08fbf3e719e2a8/gatsby.svg"}}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/03419e41a66d01bc0f315357d785c2b6/graphql.svg"}}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/6016e72a25a848010d7bf9e3ba9aedec/javascript.svg"}}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/690711e31f40c61276cfcf5c49664e61/html5.svg"}}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/39a408790e25e704f54e283ed4fd7c85/linux.svg"}}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/ced74a479e524ed267e117ff5b541dd3/nodejs.svg"}}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/c9223a9b19b8182077b39e5ca28a5a5a/mysql.svg"}}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/35ccaa8fede034bdbc5afa98a091d772/python.svg"}}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"image":{"publicURL":"/static/bc2a497a1b28798885f0c8be925780f6/react.svg"}}}}]},"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><strong>Warning: Spoilers Follow</strong></p>\n<p>A homework problem from <a href=\"https://projects.iq.harvard.edu/stat110\">Harvard's Stat 110</a> course has two chess players ready to play 7 games. The possible outcomes for each game are Win (1 point), Draw (0.5 points), and Loss (0 points). If all seven games were to be played regardless of the outcomes of the individual games, it's possible that one player could have 7 points and the other 0 points. We'll call the two players A and B.</p>\n<p><strong>(a) How many possible outcomes for the individual games are there, such that player A has a final result of 3 wins, 2 draws, and 2 losses?</strong></p>\n<p>First, we consider the ways in which A can get 4 wins in 7 games, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mfrac linethickness=\"0px\"><mn>7</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\binom{7}{3}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.245118em;vertical-align:-0.35001em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">(</span></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8951079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.3550000000000004em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.144em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">7</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.345em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">)</span></span></span></span></span></span>. Next, we consider the ways in which A can get 2 draws in the remaining 3 games, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mfrac linethickness=\"0px\"><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\binom{4}{2}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.245118em;vertical-align:-0.35001em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">(</span></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8951079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.3550000000000004em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.144em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">4</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.345em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">)</span></span></span></span></span></span>. Finally, we consider the ways in which A can get 2 losses in the remaining 2 games, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mfrac linethickness=\"0px\"><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\binom{2}{2}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.245118em;vertical-align:-0.35001em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">(</span></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8951079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.3550000000000004em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.144em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.345em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size1\">)</span></span></span></span></span></span>. This gives us</p>\n<span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mfrac linethickness=\"0px\"><mn>7</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mfrac linethickness=\"0px\"><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mo fence=\"true\">(</mo><mfrac linethickness=\"0px\"><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo fence=\"true\">)</mo></mrow><mtext> </mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext> </mtext><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo></mrow></mfrac><mtext> </mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext> </mtext><mn>210</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\binom{7}{3}\\binom{4}{2}\\binom{2}{2} \\ = \\ \\frac{7!}{3!2!2!} \\ = \\ 210</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.40003em;vertical-align:-0.95003em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">(</span></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.32144em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.314em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">3</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.677em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">7</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.686em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">)</span></span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">(</span></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.32144em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.314em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">2</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.677em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">4</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.686em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">)</span></span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">(</span></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.32144em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.314em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">2</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.677em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">2</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.686em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\"><span class=\"delimsizing size3\">)</span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\"> </span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\"> </span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.05744em;vertical-align:-0.686em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.37144em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.314em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.677em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">7</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.686em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span><span class=\"mspace\"> </span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\"> </span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span></span>\n<p>Keeping in mind that there are n! permutations of n distinct objects, and that each chess game can be thought of as a distinct object (maybe with a particular event ID number for record-keeping), we can say there are 7! permutations of 7 games to be played. For example if games 1 - 7 are given IDs sequentially starting from 1, one permutation of the 7-game tournament is 1234567. Another is 7123456. It would be tedious and demotivating to have to list all of the permutations, of course. </p>\n<p>Anyway, the middle term in the above equation <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo></mrow></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\frac{7!}{3!2!2!}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.2251079999999999em;vertical-align:-0.345em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mopen nulldelimiter\"></span><span class=\"mfrac\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8801079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.6550000000000002em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span><span class=\"mclose mtight\">!</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span><span class=\"mclose mtight\">!</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span><span class=\"mclose mtight\">!</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.394em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">7</span><span class=\"mclose mtight\">!</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.345em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span></span></span></span> can be read as the number of permutations of 7 games divided by the product of the number of permutations of games won by A, the number of games played to a draw, and the number of games lost by A.</p>\n<p><strong>(b) How many possible outcomes for the individual games are there, such that A records 4 points and B records 3 points?</strong></p>\n<p>Think of the ways in which A can get 4 points:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>4 wins, 0 draws, 3 losses (possible result 1)</li>\n<li>3 wins, 2 draws, 2 losses (possible result 2)</li>\n<li>2 wins, 4 draws, 1 loss (possible result 3)</li>\n<li>1 win, 6 draws, 0 losses (possible result 4)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Combining the possible results is straightforward.</p>\n<span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xm